	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Gnomes as Necros:  This is what I am playing right now.  I am up to level 19 at the present time.  It is a difficult combination, though not as hard as the Dark Elf Necro (I think).  Gnomes have high INT and good stats in the other categories (except strength) and are powerful necros.  There are a lot of creatures in the gnome home area to keep you gaining EXP until the lower teens at least.  Traveling is a pain.  Many of the other races hate you for being a gnome or for being a necro.  Never travel without being invisible!  You also must be careful in Inns as some of the NPC patrons will kill you on sight.  Be prepared to pay extra for food, drink and other items due to your low charisma.  Kill every orc, gnoll, or whatever in sight to improve your faction standing with the guards and merchants.  Lastly, be prepared to look at a lot of knees.  Things look different when you are very short! :-)  All in all, being a gnome necro is a fun challenge.  If you can get past the frustration of being killed by some guards and other NPC's it can be quite enjoyable.<BR>
<BR>
IMHO,<BR>
<BR>
Vinenar the Gnome Necro
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
