	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I recently heard some interesting news regarding pets and the experience they take during combat.  I have no way to verify this as I did not receive word from a staff member.  Another player who has a character on the test server informed me of a recent patch (within the past month and a half) that disables pet experience sharing when you are grouped.  If you are soloing, the pet still takes exp.  <BR>
<BR>
Just thought I'd share my thoughts.  <BR>
<BR>
Also, in response to the level 4 magician debating over playing a necromancer.  My advice?  Decide whether you want to play a good or an evil character and go from there.  Both classes have a lot of advantages/disadvantages.  In many ways a necro is more powerful than a magician.  But the main thing to keep in mind is that while the magician's pet may be somewhat inferior to the necro pet, their damage spells put necros (and most other classes) to shame.  There are only two other classes that can deliver more direct damage than a magician (Wizard and Druid), but remember that they don't ever get a pet. :)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
